  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIn the validator client, we assume that each validator only proposes a block at most once per epoch, because that's kinda how things used to be. But with v0.9, the validators are shuffled per slot, so it's possible (and quite likely) that a single validator gets shuffled to first position (and is therefore a block proposer) for more than a single slot.\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe validator client doesn't propose in all the cases where it should, because it only keeps track of a single optional block proposal slot.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe validator client should keep a vec of slots where each validator is expected to propose, and propose blocks accordingly.\r\n",
